'''Japan Shrine''' is a vibrant world by RootGentle, based on a Japanese shinto shrine. This world is a considered as a follow-up world to the [https://vrchat.com/home/world/wrld_736bad27-4663-4346-a345-26e1e859d94e "Japan Shrine" world by ITOAR]. 
It is a serene, cultural environment to wander and socialize.

This world is a legitimate sequel by the author of the first ＂Japan Shrine＂ published in 2018․

==World design and atmosphere==
Japan Shrine has dynamic lighting, and includes a day-night cycle, contributing to its realism, and allowing you to see how taisha ''(<span lang="ja">大社</span>; lit. "great shrine")'' looks under early soft morning light,  into golden hour sunsets. 

===Seasonal changes===
The world is also updated seasonally to reflect the atmosphere of the four seasons:
*Summer
*Spring
*Fall
*Winter

==Legacy and popularity==
Following the familiar Japan Shrine series, this world carries on in much the same spirit of its origin, with thespian details and designs have given way to fresh look with tempting sounds. Japan Shrine remains popular{{Citation needed}} with users in July, August, but particularly so during over-all milder weather months.

==Trivia==
* Japan Shrine was highlighted in VRChat's "Golden Week" event in 2024.

